        <h2>Optical Image Stabilisation</h2>
        <p>
          Optical Image Stabilisation (OIS) is widely recognised as the feature providing the most substantial improvement to smartphone camera quality in recent years. It allows for blur-free photographs and shake-free videos. A gyroscope sensor in the handset is used to measure jitter. An actuator between the image sensor and AutoFocus mechanism moves the lens to compensate for this motion, thus stabilising the imaging system. OIS started shipping in international smartphones in 2012 and analysts predict the market size to be 370 million units in 2017.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-2 gemini_image"></div>
    </div>
