      <div class="col-3">
        <div class="beige-circle" id="size"></div>
        <h5>Size</h5>
        <p>
          Smart metal actuators are less than a third of the height of VCM competition and therefore provide the thinnest OIS cameras.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-3">
        <div class="beige-circle" id="perfomance"></div>
        <h5>Perfomance</h5>
        <p>
          SMA material’s high driving force combined with CML’s patented control algorithms provide industry leading shake suppression performance and camera image quality.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-3">
        <div class="beige-circle" id="magnet"></div>
        <h5>Power Consumption</h5>
        <p>
          Smart metal OIS consumes around a fifth the power of VCM, extending smartphone battery life and minimising heat generation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-3">
        <div class="beige-circle" id="magnet"></div>
        <h5>Non-Magnetic</h5>
        <p>
          VCM OIS cameras contain several strong magnets to move the lens. The magnetic fields interfere with critical handset components. SMA OIS uses no magnets and generates no disruptive fields. This allows handsets to perform optimally and maximise flexibility of design.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-3">
        <div class="beige-circle" id="camera"></div>
        <h5>Dual Cameras</h5>
        <p>
          Dual cameras combine the output of two individual cameras to enhance functionality and image quality. To enable advanced capabilities more powerful cameras are required. Because SMA OIS contains no magnets, it is the only workable solution for compact dual camera designs.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-3">
        <div class="beige-circle" id="phone"></div>
        <h5>Selfie Cameras</h5>
        <p>
          The selfie camera has seen an explosion in popularity, used to take high quality stills and video. The size constraints for a front facing camera are particularly demanding. The compact and simple structure of SMA enables inclusion of OIS into selfie cameras.
        </p>
      </div>
